Example

Turning POS & SOP into NAND-NOR

NAND definition

A NAND circuit is a circuit with only negated ANDs, similarly for NOR.

You can convert anything to a NAND form or NOR, especially POS & SOP using De Morgan's theorem.

SOP to NAND

POS to NOR
